---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Investment Decision Tool | Fractal Manifold" description="A data-driven tool to help decide whether to invest in a company now or wait for a better opportunity.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/katex@0.16.9/dist/katex.min.css" />
    <script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/katex@0.16.9/dist/katex.min.js"></script>
  </Fragment>

  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="tool-page">
      <div class="tool-background">
        <div class="gradient-orb orb-1"></div>
        <div class="gradient-orb orb-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="tool-content">

          <h1 class="tool-title">
            <span class="gradient-text">Investment Decision Tool</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="tool-subtitle">A data-driven guide for portfolio investment decisions</p>

          <!-- Intro -->
          <details class="intro-details">
            <summary class="intro-summary">
              <h2>How it works</h2>
              <span class="intro-toggle-hint">Show explanation</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="intro-content">
              <p class="intro-lead">Imagine you need to pick <strong>25 companies</strong> to invest in from a pool of <strong>40 candidates</strong>, but they show up for meetings <strong>one at a time in random order</strong>. You know each company's overall quality ranking, but you must decide on the spot: invest now, or pass and hope a better one comes along?</p>
              <ul class="intro-points">
                <li><strong>The catch:</strong> You can't go back. Once you pass on a company, that slot is gone. And some companies drop out before you even meet them &mdash; their round closes or they cancel. The longer a company waits, the more likely it drops out.</li>
                <li><strong>The risk:</strong> Be too picky and you run out of options. Be too eager and you fill your portfolio with lower-ranked companies. Top-ranked companies are exponentially more valuable than lower-ranked ones.</li>
                <li><strong>This tool helps:</strong> Given the current company's quality ranking and how far along you are, it calculates whether you should invest now or wait. It uses thousands of simulated scenarios to find the optimal strategy.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Portfolio Settings -->
          <div class="tool-card">
            <div class="tool-card-label gold">Portfolio Settings</div>
            <div class="grid-basic">
              <div class="field">
                <label for="paramN">Total companies</label>
                <input type="number" id="paramN" value="40" min="5" max="200" />
              </div>
              <div class="field">
                <label for="paramK">Investments needed</label>
                <input type="number" id="paramK" value="25" min="1" max="200" />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Advanced settings (collapsible) -->
          <details class="charts-details">
            <summary class="charts-summary">
              <h2>Dropout &amp; Value Settings</h2>
              <span class="charts-toggle-hint">Show settings</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="charts-content">
              <div class="grid-params">
                <div class="field">
                  <label for="paramPMin" id="pMinLabel">Early dropout chance: 10%</label>
                  <input type="range" id="paramPMin" min="0" max="0.4" step="0.01" value="0.10" />
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <label for="paramPMax" id="pMaxLabel">Late dropout chance: 50%</label>
                  <input type="range" id="paramPMax" min="0.1" max="0.9" step="0.05" value="0.50" />
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <label for="paramBeta" id="betaLabel" data-tooltip="Controls how fast the dropout probability increases from early to late. Higher = steeper jump near the end">Dropout acceleration: 3.0</label>
                  <input type="range" id="paramBeta" min="0.5" max="6" step="0.1" value="3.0" />
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <label for="paramLambda" id="lambdaLabel" data-tooltip="How much more valuable top-ranked companies are. Higher = top companies are worth exponentially more">Quality premium: 0.06</label>
                  <input type="range" id="paramLambda" min="0.02" max="0.25" step="0.01" value="0.06" />
                </div>
              </div>
              <div id="calIndicator" class="calibrating-indicator">
                <div class="spinner"></div> Calibrating model via Monte Carlo&hellip;
              </div>
              <div class="charts-divider"></div>
              <div class="charts-row">
                <div>
                  <div class="chart-title">Dropout probability by position</div>
                  <canvas id="dropoutChart"></canvas>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="chart-title">Investment value by rank</div>
                  <canvas id="valueChart"></canvas>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Meeting Board -->
          <div class="tool-card">
            <div class="board-header">
              <div class="tool-card-label purple">Meeting Queue</div>
              <button class="btn-reset" id="resetBoard" data-tooltip="Reset order to rank and clear all states">Reset</button>
            </div>
            <div class="board-legend">
              <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot dot-unknown"></span> In queue</span>
              <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot dot-waiting"></span> Undecided</span>
              <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot dot-invested"></span> Invested</span>
              <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot dot-canceled"></span> Canceled</span>
            </div>
            <p class="board-hint">Click to change state (in queue &rarr; undecided &rarr; invested &rarr; canceled). Drag to reorder. The first grey tile is the next meeting.</p>
            <div class="board-grid" id="boardGrid"></div>
            <div class="board-current" id="boardCurrent"></div>
            <div class="derived-row">
              <div class="derived" data-tooltip="Companies you have not yet met or decided on">
                <div class="d-label">Companies left</div>
                <div class="d-value" id="derivedRemaining">40</div>
              </div>
              <div class="derived" data-tooltip="How many more investments you need to reach your target">
                <div class="d-label">Still need</div>
                <div class="d-value" id="derivedNeeded">25</div>
              </div>
              <div class="derived" data-tooltip="Total meetings resolved (invested + fell through)">
                <div class="d-label">Meetings used</div>
                <div class="d-value" id="derivedUsed">0</div>
              </div>
              <div class="derived" data-tooltip="How many more companies you can expect to actually meet, considering dropouts">
                <div class="d-label">Expected ahead</div>
                <div class="d-value" id="derivedSupply">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
              <div class="derived" data-tooltip="Portfolio quality score (0 = empty, 5 = worst full portfolio, 10 = best possible)">
                <div class="d-label">Portfolio score</div>
                <div class="d-value highlight" id="derivedScore">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Decision Result -->
          <div id="decisionBox" class="decision-box accept">
            <div class="decision-header">
              <div class="decision-icon" id="decIcon">&#x2705;</div>
              <div>
                <div class="decision-title" id="decTitle">INVEST</div>
                <div class="decision-confidence">Confidence: <span id="decConf" class="conf-high">STRONG RECOMMENDATION</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="decision-reason" id="decReason"></div>
            <div class="stat-grid">
              <div class="stat" data-tooltip="Invest in companies ranked at or better than this number">
                <div class="label">Quality bar</div>
                <div class="value" id="decThresh">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat" data-tooltip="Extra meetings you expect beyond the minimum needed. Higher = more room to be picky">
                <div class="label">Breathing room</div>
                <div class="value" id="decSlack">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat" data-tooltip="Remaining companies you have not yet met">
                <div class="label">Companies left</div>
                <div class="value" id="decSlotsLeft">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat" data-tooltip="How urgent it is to start accepting. LOW means you can afford to be selective">
                <div class="label">Urgency</div>
                <div class="value" id="decRisk">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
              <div class="stat" data-tooltip="Auto-calibrated parameter controlling how selective you can be (higher = pickier)">
                <div class="label">Selectivity</div>
                <div class="value highlight" id="decAlpha">&mdash;</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="safety-bar">
              <div class="bar-header">
                <span class="l">Portfolio completion confidence</span>
                <span class="r" id="safetyPct">&mdash;</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bar-bg"><div class="bar-fill" id="safetyFill" style="width:80%;background:#10B981"></div></div>
              <div class="bar-zones"><span>Must accept most</span><span>Can be selective</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Mathematical Model (collapsible) -->
          <details class="math-details">
            <summary class="math-summary">
              <h2>Mathematical Model</h2>
              <span class="toggle-hint">Show formulas</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="math-content-wrapper">
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">State Variables</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math1"></div>
                <div class="math-note">These track where you are: how many investments you have made (<em>i</em>) and how many meetings fell through (<em>c</em>). Everything else is derived from these two numbers.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Dropout Probability (Exponential)</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math2"></div>
                <div class="math-note">The chance a company drops out grows from p<sub>min</sub> (early meetings, ~10%) to p<sub>max</sub> (late meetings, ~50%). The parameter &beta; controls how sharply the curve rises &mdash; higher &beta; means most of the increase happens near the end.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Expected Future Meetings</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math3"></div>
                <div class="math-note">For each remaining company, we calculate the probability it actually shows up (1 minus its dropout probability) and add them all up. This gives the expected number of meetings you will still have.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Breathing Room (Slack)</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math4"></div>
                <div class="math-note">The gap between how many meetings you expect to have and how many you absolutely need. When this hits zero, you must invest in everyone you meet &mdash; there is no room to be selective.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Acceptance Threshold</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math5"></div>
                <div class="math-note">The quality cutoff. Any company ranked at or better (lower number) than this threshold gets a green light. When you have lots of breathing room, the bar is high (selective). As it shrinks, the bar drops smoothly until you must accept anyone.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Value Function (Exponential)</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="mathVal"></div>
                <div class="math-note">Top-ranked companies are exponentially more valuable. The parameter &lambda; controls how steep this is. With &lambda;=0.06, the #1 company is worth about 10&times; the #40 company, making quality important but not overwhelmingly so.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Optimal Selectivity &mdash; Monte Carlo Calibration</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math6"></div>
                <div class="math-note">The model runs thousands of simulated portfolios to find the best balance between quality and safety. The total portfolio value (using the exponential value function) is multiplied by the probability of actually completing the portfolio. The &alpha; that maximizes this product is the optimal one.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="math-block">
                <div class="math-label">Decision Rule</div>
                <div class="math-content" id="math7"></div>
                <div class="math-note">Simple: if the company's rank is at or below the quality bar, invest.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  main { padding-top: 80px; }

  .tool-page { position: relative; min-height: 100vh; padding: 3rem 0 4rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .tool-background { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; z-index: -1; }
  .gradient-orb { position: absolute; border-radius: 50%; filter: blur(100px); opacity: 0.15; }
  .orb-1 { width: 450px; height: 450px; background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-gold), transparent); top: 3%; right: 8%; }
  .orb-2 { width: 500px; height: 500px; background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-purple), transparent); bottom: 15%; left: -5%; }
  .tool-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .tool-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.8rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; text-align: center; }
  .gradient-text { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-gold) 0%, var(--color-gold) 30%, var(--color-purple) 70%, var(--color-purple) 100%); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
  .tool-subtitle { text-align: center; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  /* Intro (collapsible) */
  .intro-details { background: rgba(26,26,26,0.5); border: 1px solid rgba(243,158,11,0.1); border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .intro-summary { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .intro-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .intro-summary:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  .intro-summary h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  .intro-toggle-hint { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); transition: color 0.2s; }
  .intro-details[open] .intro-toggle-hint { color: var(--color-text-secondary); }
  .intro-content { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; }
  .intro-lead { color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .intro-lead strong { color: var(--color-text); }
  .intro-points { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .intro-points li { color: var(--color-text-secondary); padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem 1.5rem; position: relative; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .intro-points li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.85rem; width: 6px; height: 6px; background: var(--color-gold); border-radius: 50%; }
  .intro-points li strong { color: var(--color-text); }

  /* Cards */
  .tool-card { background: rgba(26,26,26,0.5); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; backdrop-filter: blur(8px); }
  .tool-card-label { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.7rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1.5px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .tool-card-label.gold { color: var(--color-gold); }
  .tool-card-label.purple { color: var(--color-purple); }
  .grid-basic { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .grid-params { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
  .charts-divider { margin-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }

  /* Fields */
  .field label { display: block; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .field input[type="number"] { width: 100%; padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); color: var(--color-text); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; outline: none; transition: border-color 0.2s; }
  .field input[type="number"]:focus { border-color: var(--color-gold); }
  .field input[type="range"] { -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; width: 100%; height: 6px; border-radius: 3px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); outline: none; margin-top: 0.5rem; cursor: pointer; }
  .field input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb { -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-gold); cursor: pointer; border: 2px solid var(--color-bg); }
  .field input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb { width: 18px; height: 18px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-gold); cursor: pointer; border: 2px solid var(--color-bg); }

  /* Charts collapsible */
  .charts-details { background: rgba(26,26,26,0.5); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .charts-summary { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .charts-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .charts-summary:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  .charts-summary h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-gold); letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  .charts-toggle-hint { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); transition: color 0.2s; }
  .charts-details[open] .charts-toggle-hint { color: var(--color-text-secondary); }
  .charts-content { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; }
  .charts-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  .chart-title { font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .charts-content canvas { width: 100%; height: 170px; display: block; }
  .calibrating-indicator { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--color-purple); font-weight: 600; display: none; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .calibrating-indicator.active { display: flex; }
  .spinner { width: 12px; height: 12px; border: 2px solid var(--color-purple); border-top-color: transparent; border-radius: 50%; animation: spin 0.6s linear infinite; }
  @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  /* Board */
  .board-header { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
  .board-header .tool-card-label { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .btn-reset { padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); color: var(--color-text-muted); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  .btn-reset:hover { border-color: var(--color-gold); color: var(--color-gold); background: rgba(245,158,11,0.08); }

  .board-legend { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin: 0.75rem 0 0.4rem; }
  .legend-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.3rem; font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .legend-dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); }
  .dot-unknown { background: transparent; }
  .dot-waiting { background: #92600a; border-color: #b8860b; }
  .dot-invested { background: #0d6b4a; border-color: #10B981; }
  .dot-canceled { background: #7f1d1d; border-color: #EF4444; }

  .board-hint { font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-style: italic; }

  .board-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; min-height: 40px; }

  .board-grid :global(.tile) {
    width: 48px; height: 48px; border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    cursor: grab; user-select: none;
    transition: transform 0.1s, box-shadow 0.15s, opacity 0.15s;
    position: relative;
    border: 2px solid;
    color: #FFFFFF;
  }
  .board-grid :global(.tile:hover) { transform: scale(1.1); z-index: 2; }
  .board-grid :global(.tile:active) { cursor: grabbing; transform: scale(0.95); }

  .board-grid :global(.tile.unknown) { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
  .board-grid :global(.tile.waiting) { background: #78520d; border-color: #d4a017; color: #FEF3C7; }
  .board-grid :global(.tile.invested) { background: #065f46; border-color: #10B981; color: #D1FAE5; }
  .board-grid :global(.tile.canceled) { background: #7f1d1d; border-color: #EF4444; color: #FEE2E2; }

  .board-grid :global(.tile.current-meeting) { box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px #FBBF24, 0 0 14px rgba(245,158,11,0.4); border-color: #FBBF24; }
  .board-grid :global(.tile.dragging) { opacity: 0.3; }

  .board-current { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(245,158,11,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.15); }
  .board-current strong { color: #FBBF24; }
  .board-current.no-meeting { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); color: var(--color-text-muted); }

  /* Derived row */
  .derived-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.6rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; padding-top: 0.75rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
  .derived { flex: 1; min-width: 70px; padding: 0.5rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); text-align: center; position: relative; }
  .derived .d-label { font-size: 0.58rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  .derived .d-value { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; margin-top: 0.1rem; }
  .derived .d-value.danger { color: #EF4444; }
  .derived .d-value.warn { color: var(--color-gold); }
  .derived .d-value.highlight { color: var(--color-purple); }

  /* Tooltips */
  [data-tooltip] { position: relative; cursor: help; }
  [data-tooltip]::after { content: attr(data-tooltip); position: absolute; bottom: calc(100% + 8px); left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; background: var(--color-bg-secondary); border: 1px solid rgba(243,158,11,0.2); border-radius: 8px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.72rem; line-height: 1.4; width: max-content; max-width: 220px; text-align: center; opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; transition: opacity 0.2s; z-index: 10; font-weight: 400; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: 0; }
  [data-tooltip]:hover::after { opacity: 1; }

  /* Decision box */
  .decision-box { border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid; transition: all 0.3s; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .decision-box.accept { background: rgba(16,185,129,0.06); border-color: rgba(16,185,129,0.25); }
  .decision-box.reject { background: rgba(245,158,11,0.06); border-color: rgba(245,158,11,0.25); }
  .decision-box.neutral { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
  .decision-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .decision-icon { width: 56px; height: 56px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1.5rem; border: 2px solid; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .decision-box.accept .decision-icon { background: rgba(16,185,129,0.12); border-color: #10B981; }
